<title>SRI LANKA: Weather-Showers seen in many parts of Sri Lanka.</title>
<headline>Weather-Showers seen in many parts of Sri Lanka.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-05-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sri Lanka's metereological department released the following rainfall figures for 24 hours ending Monday morning</p>
<p>Hydro catchment areas (in mm):</p>
<p>    Bowathenna		0</p>
<p>    Canyon		    3.8</p>
<p>    Castlereigh	     44.2</p>
<p>    Kotmale		   8</p>
<p>    Laxapana		  47.2</p>
<p>    Moussakele		4.3</p>
<p>    Norton		    4.3</p>
<p>    Randenigala	     1.1</p>
<p>    Victoria		  24.2</p>
<p>    Samanalawewa	    13.5</p>
<p>    Ukuwela		   7.5</p>
<p>    Rantembe		  7.6</p>
<p>The department forecast morning showers along the southwestern coastal areas and thundershowers at several places elsewhere during the afternoon or evening.</p>
